A '''rig standpipe''' is a solid metal pipe attached to the side of a [[drilling rig|drilling rig's]] [[derrick (lifting device)|derrick]] that is a part of its [[drilling mud]] system. It is used to conduct [[drilling fluid]] from the mud [[pump]]s to the [[kelly hose]]. Bull plugs, pressure [[transducer]]s and [[valve]]s are found on the rig standpipe.

